00:14:36.220 --> 00:14:37.803
Was this one fourth
around the circle?

00:14:37.803 --> 00:14:38.617
Was this one half?

00:14:38.617 --> 00:14:40.700
And this is actually one
fourth around the circle,

00:14:40.700 --> 00:14:41.557
right over here?

00:14:41.557 --> 00:14:43.640
But now it becomes obvious
if you write it in tau.

00:14:46.800 --> 00:14:50.380
Pi over 2 is the same
thing as to tau over 4.

00:14:50.380 --> 00:14:53.510
Pi is the same thing
as to tau over 2.

00:14:53.510 --> 00:15:02.300
3 pi over 2 is 3 pi-- oh,
sorry, 3 tau over 4, 3/4 tau.

00:15:02.300 --> 00:15:04.200
And then one revolution is tau.

00:15:04.200 --> 00:15:07.010
And then immediately, now
when you look at it this way,

00:15:07.010 --> 00:15:09.250
you know exactly where you
are in the unit circle.

00:15:09.250 --> 00:15:10.750
You're one fourth
around the unit circle,

00:15:10.750 --> 00:15:12.333
you're halfway around
the unit circle,

00:15:12.333 --> 00:15:14.390
you're 3/4 of the way
around the unit circle.

00:15:14.390 --> 00:15:17.290
And then you're all the
way around the unit circle.

00:15:17.290 --> 00:15:20.030
And so the last thing
that I think the strong pi

00:15:20.030 --> 00:15:22.100
defenders would say
is well, look Sal,

00:15:22.100 --> 00:15:26.330
you just pointed out one of
the most beautiful identities

00:15:26.330 --> 00:15:28.300
or formulas in mathematics.

00:15:28.300 --> 00:15:31.670
How does tau hold up to this?

00:15:31.670 --> 00:15:34.380
Well, let's just try it
