00:15:34.380 --> 00:15:41.490
So if we take e to the i tau,
that will give us cosine of tau

00:15:41.490 --> 00:15:44.520
plus i sine of tau.

00:15:44.520 --> 00:15:47.210
And once again, let's just
think about what this is.

00:15:47.210 --> 00:15:51.580
Tau radians means we've gone all
the way around the unit circle.

00:15:51.580 --> 00:15:54.570
So cosine of tau--
remember, we're

00:15:54.570 --> 00:15:56.290
back at the beginning
of the unit circle

00:15:56.290 --> 00:16:01.200
right over here-- so cosine of
tau is going to be equal to 1.

00:16:01.200 --> 00:16:04.115
And then sine of
tau is equal to 0.

00:16:07.340 --> 00:16:14.430
So e to the i tau is equal to 1.

00:16:14.430 --> 00:16:16.230
And I'll leave it
